                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12664860" author="stack" created="Sat, 17 Jan 2009 18:55:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Broaden the issue to making it so users can choose codec.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Over in &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/Hbase/PerformanceEvaluation#0_19_0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/Hbase/PerformanceEvaluation#0_19_0&lt;/a&gt;, I tested the DefaultCodec (zlib, using native encoder/decoder) and found that random reads are horrid, writes just a bit slower and scans about the same.  I wonder how lzo would change this?  Perhaps scanning and writes would run as fast as non-compressed and random reads would come up close to non-compressed data?  I did notice that block compression made for less regions &amp;#8211; about half &amp;#8211; and this was with the PE data which does its best to foil good compression.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12699250" author="stack" created="Wed, 15 Apr 2009 16:03:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;http://code.google.com/p/hadoop-gpl-compression/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://code.google.com/p/hadoop-gpl-compression/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12711282" author="stack" created="Wed, 20 May 2009 18:31:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ryan made this work, and he doc&apos;d it: &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/UsingLzoCompression&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/UsingLzoCompression&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12711284" author="stack" created="Wed, 20 May 2009 18:32:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1379&quot; title=&quot;Make KeyValue implement Writable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1379&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1379&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
